Jennifer Frazier, copy to Jeffrey Patterson and James Grant.

Quick update ahead of our call, with one ask at the bottom. The specification=
 is approved and has not moved since, which makes the approaches cleaner than=
 they usually are at this stage. Jeffrey Patterson has the market map at the =
point where it is useful rather than merely long. We are working through the =
priority names now and I have made first contact with a good share of them.

Two things worth knowing early. Interest is real, but the profile question is=
 not settled. The people who match the specification most exactly are already=
 sitting on two boards and are the hardest to move; the people with the most =
capacity are a step earlier in their careers than the specification implies. =
James Grant and I would rather test that with you now than surface it in a sl=
ate. Nothing here is off track for Sanchez-Baker at this point. It is the ord=
inary shape of the market for a seat like this one.

The ask: we need the directors who will vote available for candidate conversa=
tions, not only for the interviews at the end. The candidates worth having ar=
e asking who they would be sitting with, and that question gets answered by a=
 person or it gets answered by silence. If Sanchez-Baker can give us dates no=
w, I will build the calendar around them.

Jason Bell
